<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include("./components/_head", { title: 'About' }) %>
<body class="flex flex-col min-h-screen">
    <%- include("./components/_header") %>

    <main class="flex-grow max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
        <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-8">About BasicSSG</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/basic-ssg">BasicSSG</a> was born from the practices I used to build sites.
                Sometimes you may have complex structures, where React, Hugo or other builders may shine better. But for marketing, SEO and simple sites, all this bundling adds complexity
                and load times. BasicSSG has no dependencies. Just and idea to structure and tap in on what you need.
            </p>
            
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-4">Our Core Philosophy</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-4 text-slate-600">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></span>
                    <span><strong>No Frameworks:</strong> No React, Vue, or Svelte. Just EJS templates that compile to plain HTML. I mean, you can maybe do some plugin to add React, but then I suppose just use NextJS, or whatever.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></span>
                    <span><strong>Plug and Play:</strong> Use only what you need. Assets, Sitemap, Tailwindâ€”all optional plugins.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></span>
                    <span><strong>Developer First:</strong> Fast builds, simple configuration, and full control over your output. You understand how things operate. Extend the architecture as you need.</span>
                </li>
            </ul>

        </article>
    </main>

    <%- include("./components/_footer") %>
</body>
</html>
